sales vs segment analysis¶

In [393]:
segment_2011=merged_df_final[['sales','segment']]
segment_2011['year'] = 2011
segment_2012=merged_df1[['sales','segment']]
segment_2012['year'] = 2012
segment_2013=merged_df2[['sales','segment']]
segment_2013['year'] = 2013
segment_2014=merged_df3[['sales','segment']]
segment_2014['year'] = 2014
segment_final = pd.concat([segment_2011, segment_2012, segment_2013, segment_2014])
segment_final.dropna()
df_pivot = segment_final.pivot_table(index='segment', columns='year', values='sales').reset_index()
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.countplot(data=segment_final,x='segment',hue='year',palette=['#842d72','#fbdfb7','#ee316b','#ffb037'])
plt.xlabel('Segment')
plt.ylabel('Sales')
plt.title('Sales vs Segment Comparison for 2011,2012,2013 and 2014')
plt.legend(title='Year')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Calculate Total Sales of Each Year¶

In [404]:
files = ['trans_fact_2011.csv', 'trans_fact_2012.csv', 'trans_fact_2013.csv', 'trans_fact_2014.csv']
data = pd.concat((pd.read_csv(file) for file in files), ignore_index=True)
data['order_date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['order_date'], format='%d-%m-%Y', errors='coerce')
data['ship_date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['ship_date'], format='%d-%m-%Y', errors='coerce')
data = data.dropna(subset=['order_date', 'ship_date'])
data['year'] = data['order_date'].dt.year
yearly_data = data.groupby('year')['sales'].sum()

for year, sales in yearly_data.items():
    print(f"Year {year}: {np.format_float_positional(sales, precision=4)}")  # Print with no decimal places

Year 2011: 2259450.8955
Year 2012: 2677438.6944
Year 2013: 3405746.4494
Year 2014: 4299865.8706
